                    text: "The ENR engine is generally robust with proper maintenance. Its primary long-term consideration is intake valve carbon buildup, common to many GDI engines. Regular oil changes with the correct specification and periodic highway driving to clean the GPF are crucial for longevity. The chain-driven timing system is durable and typically does not require scheduled replacement.",
